Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 760 "The Romance \NNovel with the Unexpected Conclusion (Part 2)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.05,0:00:05.35,DCMain,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, Sonoko, and I went to hang out \Nwith Sera at the hotel she lives in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.82,0:00:09.73,DCMain,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,On our way home, a homicide \Noccurred on a lower floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.25,0:00:14.50,Author,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(220,0)}Hiura Keigo (48)\NAuthor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.28,0:00:14.49,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}M-Maybe it has something\Nto do with that fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.50,0:00:19.19,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,This morning, my department received a fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.12,0:00:22.45,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't fire the \Nassistant, you'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.19,0:00:22.45,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,It said we'd regret it if we \Ndidn't fire his assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.45,0:00:25.05,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.26,0:00:28.46,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You had plenty of opportunities to tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.21,0:00:32.21,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.41,0:00:36.09,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.09,0:00:37.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...is this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.26,0:00:43.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The hidden lines on the palm are the fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.01,0:00:45.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The deduction catches fire \Non the line to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.02,0:00:47.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The contents of the novel \Nbring us closer to the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:49.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who is the girl who looks like Sera?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.11,0:00:52.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.37,0:00:54.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:41.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(405,1)}The Romance Novel with the \NUnexpected Conclusion\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.99,0:02:39.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Romance Novel with the \NUnexpected Conclusion, Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.44,0:02:44.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:47.52,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I wanted \Nto confirm with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.79,0:02:48.71,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.71,0:02:51.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The caps for the shampoo and \Nconditioner are missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.93,0:02:53.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The ones from the victim's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.36,0:02:54.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.61,0:02:58.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They're amenities that \Ncome with the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.15,0:03:01.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't find them in the drain, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:04.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We only entered the main entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:07.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then you weren't the ones \Nwho knocked over the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.93,0:03:08.75,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The table?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.03,0:03:14.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the room was undisturbed, but \Nsomehow just the table was knocked over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:18.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A can of beer that we believe \Nwas sitting on top of it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.03,0:03:20.54,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,had fallen on top of the victim's suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.54,0:03:25.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim's clothes inside the \Nsuitcase are covered in beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.33,0:03:27.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of suitcase is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.52,0:03:30.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It was pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:33.87,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't much inside it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.87,0:03:35.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What was inside the suitcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.70,0:03:40.69,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,In addition to clothes, we found \Nmakeup, a tablet, and a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.69,0:03:42.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.43,0:03:46.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There was an old postcard in one of \Nthe backpack's inside pockets, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.56,0:03:47.49,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,An old...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:48.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...postcard?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:04:05.81,Letter,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(750,900)}What a cute story.\NWhen I write\Na story like this,\Nmaybe I'll name the\Nheroine after you.\NHiura Keigo
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.15,0:03:50.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.27,0:03:52.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It was postmarked twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.44,0:03:55.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The sender was Hiura-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.10,0:03:57.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It says, "What a cute story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.47,0:04:04.23,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,When I write a story like this, maybe \NI'll name the heroine after you."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.23,0:04:09.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But it's addressed to Ota \NJun, not Mizunashi Chiaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:09.14,Letter2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,0)}Ota Jun-sama
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.14,0:04:10.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,O-Ota Jun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.84,0:04:18.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the heroine's name from Hiura-sensei's\N"The Phone, the Ocean, and I."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:18.32,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Phone, The Ocean, and I \NHiura Keigo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.64,0:04:19.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:20.61,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:23.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.27,0:04:29.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,One day, the heroine finds an old \Nscratched up cell phone on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.73,0:04:31.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Strangely enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:37.70,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,the phone is a new, unreleased model she\Nwas planning to buy the following week.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.70,0:04:45.47,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,While she's looking at the phone, she \Nreceives an e-mail asking how old she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:45.47,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,How old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.87,0:04:47.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:50.13,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.13,0:04:54.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,the heroine responds, "I won't tell \Nyou my personal information, idiot!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.35,0:04:58.20,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,She receives the response "You started \Ntalking like that in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.20,0:05:00.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That brings back memories."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:02.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The sender correctly guesses \Na bunch of other things, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.75,0:05:06.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,like the results of that day's\Nsoccer or baseball games.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.53,0:05:09.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I-I-Is it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.41,0:05:10.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:15.54,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is sending her messages with a time \Ntransference device using her future phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.54,0:05:18.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A time transference device?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:19.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.11,0:05:21.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's basically a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.42,0:05:26.58,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the heroine learns the world becomes \Na mess a few years in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.58,0:05:30.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,she begins changing the future \Nlittle by little to prevent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.72,0:05:33.06,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Really? That sounds kind of interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.06,0:05:34.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.63,0:05:37.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the heroine asks the person,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.98,0:05:42.81,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Who are you? What is your \Nrelationship with me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.81,0:05:47.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they always answer \N"The phone, the ocean, and I."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:51.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What the heck? \NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:56.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The heroine thought it was gibberish at \Nfirst, but she finally figured it out recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.64,0:06:01.59,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,She responds to the sender with \N"The phone, the ocean, and I."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:06:01.59,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The phone, the ocean, and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:02.78,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.78,0:06:06.62,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is finally going to be \Nrevealed in next week's final chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:09.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:13.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He's a bold writer, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.98,0:06:16.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have any time left,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.10,0:06:23.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but he invited the editors watching him \Ninto his room for lunch to win them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.54,0:06:25.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If I were in his situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.43,0:06:30.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I would probably shave my head in \Ndesperation and ask for more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:35.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, he already has a shaved head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:41.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did the writer already go back to his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.01,0:06:42.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.05,0:06:44.51,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Since he's a suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.51,0:06:49.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,we're having him wait in front of his \Nroom until forensics is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:52.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Then they should still be in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:53.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.42,0:06:58.02,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The alibi trick and misprint error...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:07:01.31,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,...that failed to revise this crime novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.80,0:07:12.12,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.12,0:07:14.73,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going to \Nkeep searching my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.73,0:07:16.54,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:20.67,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,The body was found in her\Nroom directly below this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.67,0:07:24.66,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,and she was killed around 3:30 PM, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.66,0:07:31.09,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I was in this room at that time, and \NI even have people vouching for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:32.99,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.99,0:07:34.55,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.34,0:07:41.44,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,From 3:00 until around 4:30, \NI was eating in Hiura-sensei's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.74,0:07:47.93,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He was taking a bath at the \Ntime and didn't eat with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.93,0:07:50.82,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no way he could \Nhave gotten out of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.21,0:07:55.71,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,We were eating at the \Ntable facing the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.77,0:08:00.83,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But if he had a rope, he could climb \Ndown from the balcony to the room below.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:03.58,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:06.70,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,This is the 30th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:08.84,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not 007.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.84,0:08:12.84,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,A simple author like myself \Ncould never pull that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.19,0:08:16.94,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you can see the \Nbalcony from the table, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:18.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.60,0:08:23.20,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to take any \Nmore of my personal time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.20,0:08:26.55,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,you'll have to tell me how I got out of here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.55,0:08:28.61,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,when the crime was committed \Nand how I got back up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.04,0:08:33.82,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,There was no need for\Nyou to leave or return.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.01,0:08:44.13,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You invited the victim to this \Nroom and killed her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.13,0:08:46.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The victim was in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.61,0:08:48.50,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:53.45,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,The editors would have noticed \NMinazuki-kun coming to this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.45,0:08:55.26,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,They recognize her face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.26,0:08:57.52,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't come here, did she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.52,0:08:59.19,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.19,0:09:00.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.48,0:09:01.35,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:04.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There were lots of people \Nbringing delivery food, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.76,0:09:05.81,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.22,0:09:09.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think anyone would be \Nfooled if Minazuki-san
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:12.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,disguised herself as a delivery person
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.24,0:09:15.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and changed her hairstyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.34,0:09:21.52,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,M-Maybe, but everyone\Nleft once we paid them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.52,0:09:23.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:27.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about the wine\Non top of that desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.35,0:09:29.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you ordered a decanter,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.80,0:09:32.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't be strange for the delivery \Nperson to enter the room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:35.54,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.54,0:09:39.68,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura-sensei asked the person who delivered \Nthe wine to pour it into a decanter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.68,0:09:44.52,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,It was a bellhop wearing glasses \Nwith her hair tied back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.52,0:09:45.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A bellhop?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.32,0:09:50.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see that bellhop leave the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:51.85,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.85,0:09:53.78,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,We were too busy eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:55.18,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.18,0:09:56.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's what he wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:58.28,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.78,0:10:01.21,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you had been waiting outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.21,0:10:07.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you would've checked how many people \Nentered and how many left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.45,0:10:12.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura-sensei may have tried to escape \Ndisguised as a delivery person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:19.16,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But once he invited you into the room, \Nyou stopped checking as diligently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.16,0:10:27.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who entered, you just had\Nto make sure Hiura-sensei didn't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.00,0:10:31.49,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it didn't bother you that\Nthe bellhop who brought the wine
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.49,0:10:34.98,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,entered the room and never came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:38.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Was the bellhop Minazuki-san, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:40.15,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.15,0:10:44.32,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,While the editors were \Neating in the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:50.42,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,he told the victim to go to the \Nbathroom and killed her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.11,0:11:01.38,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He probably chose the bathroom since she \Nwould take off her bellhop clothes herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:05.14,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The body was wearing a bathrobe which \Nwould be easy to put on someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:09.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why did the victim \Ndisguise herself as a bellhop?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:12.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She's his assistant. She could have \Nstopped by without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.23,0:11:14.90,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Because they were suspected of being lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.25,0:11:22.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If the editors saw her enter, who knows\Nwhat the magazines would write next?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.72,0:11:25.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He asked her to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.32,0:11:30.41,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,What an interesting trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.15,0:11:37.92,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to use it if I ever\Nwrite a mystery novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.73,0:11:40.92,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me one thing, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.60,0:11:47.68,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,How did I move the body from \Nthis room to the one below?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.82,0:11:54.62,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I left this room around 5:30 PM,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.62,0:11:59.42,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,thirty minutes before the bellboy \Ndiscovered the body downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.42,0:12:02.28,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Was I carrying a body then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:03.63,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.63,0:12:05.99,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,You were only holding your wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.30,0:12:12.21,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing between the time I \Nleft and the bellboy started shouting?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:17.38,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,I-I was reading the manuscript you \Nhad written in front of your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:23.13,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I can't write your mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.35,0:12:25.68,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.15,0:12:28.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.34,0:12:32.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're ready now. Do it, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:35.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,T-Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:36.80,DCMain,FORENSICS,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:40.64,DCMain,FORENSICS,0000,0000,0000,,Something just fell on the \Nbalcony from the floor above.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.64,0:12:41.74,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.13,0:12:43.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The balcony?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.96,0:12:47.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:49.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A suitcase!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.97,0:12:53.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why did this fall from upstairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.69,0:12:54.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:57.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Open the suitcase!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.68,0:13:01.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.05,0:13:11.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,T-Two bags of rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.73,0:13:14.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Each bag is thirty kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:15.90,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,All together, that's sixty kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.90,0:13:18.40,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's roughly the weight of one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.73,0:13:21.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did he put the body in a suitcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:22.78,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.78,0:13:26.24,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Climbing down on a rope would be scary,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:28.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but passing a rope through the handle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.60,0:13:31.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,of a suitcase containing the \Nbody and lowering it is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:36.89,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You can swing the suitcase \Nonto the balcony below.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.89,0:13:42.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't tie the rope to the handle,\Nyou can pull it back up by one of the ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.65,0:13:46.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the suitcase \Nin the victim's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:50.18,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He brought it to move the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:55.20,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The backpack inside the suitcase \Nwas probably her actual luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.20,0:13:58.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He removed the contents and \Nstuffed her inside the suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.59,0:14:00.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.01,0:14:00.61,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.82,0:14:06.49,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura-sensei strangled the victim in the\Nbathroom after inviting her to his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.49,0:14:13.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,stuffed her inside the suitcase naked, \Nwaited for the editors to finish and leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:18.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and lowered the suitcase containing her \Nbody to the room below from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:26.48,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Then he handed out the finished \Nmanuscripts to the waiting editors,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:32.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and said he would think about how to finish \Nhis book while buying cigarettes around 5:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:37.71,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He entered the victim's room using \Nthe room key he stole from her,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:42.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,dressed her in a bathrobe, and \Nplaced her body near the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.03,0:14:47.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The bellboy instructed\Nto deliver champagne
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.36,0:14:50.08,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,to her room at exactly 6:00 \Ndiscovered her body for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.01,0:14:56.97,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He spilled beer inside the suitcase \Nto cover the wetness and smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.97,0:15:01.29,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He hastily stuffed the body inside the \Nsuitcase before her hair had dried.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.77,0:15:05.64,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably wet and\Nsmelled like shampoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.64,0:15:09.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't he dry her hair before \Nputting her inside the suitcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.75,0:15:11.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Surely he had the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:13.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he wouldn't dry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.23,0:15:20.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The editors would've thought it strange \Nif they heard the sound of the hair dryer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.53,0:15:22.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.09,0:15:23.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He has a shaved head.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:31.33,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura-sensei took the caps off the bottles\Nin the victim's room for the same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.33,0:15:38.75,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You had to replace the caps the victim\Nwashed down the drain after she used yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.14,0:15:42.32,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, there's no reason \Nfor you to use shampoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.23,0:15:45.38,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,So you may still have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.58,0:15:48.88,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The shampoo and conditioner caps.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.29,0:15:55.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming you didn't throw \Nthem away on your way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:01.68,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you did,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.68,0:16:05.20,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,a bellhop uniform was \Nfound inside a paper bag
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.20,0:16:08.62,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,in the garbage can in the elevator \Nhall on the floor below.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.62,0:16:10.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? How did it get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.81,0:16:13.83,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,His hands were empty when he left his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:18.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He was wearing them underneath \Nthe clothes he's wearing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:23.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He took them off on the \Nlanding, put them in a bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.76,0:16:26.21,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and threw them away before \Nthe body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.21,0:16:28.67,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You should find sweat, skin,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.24,0:16:35.47,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and fingerprints from the victim and \NHiura-san on the bellhop uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.18,0:16:48.25,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't throw them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.25,0:16:51.65,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried someone might be watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:55.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You admit you did it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.05,0:16:56.45,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:17:00.62,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to get away with it by\Nsending the threatening fax,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.62,0:17:04.39,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm not a mystery writer after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.39,0:17:06.42,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.89,0:17:11.34,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,She was a talented assistant. \NYou said she had revived your career!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.60,0:17:14.39,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.39,0:17:18.85,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Without her, I can't write another line.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.85,0:17:21.15,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.15,0:17:25.80,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Was she actually your lover and \Ndemanding you get divorced?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.80,0:17:27.37,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,No. It was the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.37,0:17:28.10,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.54,0:17:32.95,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times I approached her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.95,0:17:35.36,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,she would always say it would upset my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:43.87,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She took a bath because \NI told her she smelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.87,0:17:54.01,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Phone, the Ocean, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:50.28,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She came to my room to discuss my novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.79,0:17:54.01,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura Keigo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.28,0:17:53.88,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,the final scene of "The \NPhone, the Ocean, and I."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.54,0:17:58.13,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Then that novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:00.29,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.29,0:18:01.39,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:04.98,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She came up with most of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.98,0:18:07.82,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,It was based on an old fan letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.82,0:18:10.40,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You can't even call it my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.79,0:18:12.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A fan letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.26,0:18:13.54,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.54,0:18:18.43,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,While cleaning, I discovered an old fan \Nletter from a grade school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.43,0:18:22.16,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to write a novel \Nbased on the included story,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.56,0:18:28.03,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,using Ota Jun, the name of the \Nsender, as the name of my heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:31.65,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,It began when I told her about the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.65,0:18:35.25,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She asked me to let her choose the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.25,0:18:39.68,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She would meticulously revise my writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.21,0:18:44.92,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She made the novel \Nspectacular, but I didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:51.12,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,understand why she worked so hard on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:58.60,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I asked, she would smile \Nand say I would understand eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:04.28,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Then a weekly magazine \Naccused us of being lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.84,0:19:06.89,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,That was when I became certain!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:12.91,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,This woman intended to steal my family, \Nmy status, my honor, and my money from me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.91,0:19:15.46,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,and destroy me completely!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.75,0:19:17.88,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why would she do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.30,0:19:20.04,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.04,0:19:23.08,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be quite the \Nplayboy when I was younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.08,0:19:25.39,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I must have done something \Nto make her hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.42,0:19:32.15,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I'm relieved you caught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:35.62,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Though I meant to reveal the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:38.59,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,of "The Phone, the Ocean,\Nand I" in the final scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:42.16,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I killed her before I could \Nask her what it meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:43.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It means "I love you."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.83,0:19:44.53,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.54,0:19:51.72,Phone,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(910,730)}Phone                     Ocean                        I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:49.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If you translate the words \N"telephone," "sea,"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:51.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and "I" into English \Nand read them backwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.59,0:19:54.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}you get "I sea tel."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.72,0:20:00.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the heroine's boyfriend or \Nhusband was sending her messages
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.75,0:20:04.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,from the future on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:08.72,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's no way a child's \Nexplanation could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.28,0:20:11.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.03,0:20:13.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it was a child who \Noriginally came up with the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.20,0:20:19.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Similarly, if you look at Minazuki Chiaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:25.66,June,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1322,895)}Minazuki > June
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:25.66,Autumn,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1322,895)}Chiaki > Autumn
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.27,0:20:22.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"minazuki" is another word for \Nthe sixth month, or "June".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:24.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The "aki" from Chiaki is "Autumn".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.63,0:20:29.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you read them backwards, you \Nget Autumn Jun, or Ota Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:29.16,Autumn,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ota Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.49,0:20:33.16,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then... was she...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:37.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Ota Jun was her pen name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.60,0:20:40.40,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Once you learned the meaning of \N"The Phone, the Ocean, and I,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:42.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you would realize that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.66,0:20:44.68,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.09,0:20:46.93,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.30,0:20:59.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she just wanted you to make \Nher childhood dream come true
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.28,0:21:03.29,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,in the best way possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.79,0:22:28.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,"I love you," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.67,0:22:30.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.43,0:22:33.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Her boyfriend was sending her \Nmessages from the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.28,0:22:33.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.97,0:22:36.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Sera-no-neechan said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.36,0:22:39.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But couldn't it have been a stalker?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.79,0:22:40.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.26,0:22:44.96,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ruin it by saying something weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.86,0:22:52.85,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.85,0:22:53.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.24,0:22:56.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.48,0:23:02.96,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,A listening device?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.46,0:23:07.74,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's from the end of his glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.21,0:23:09.94,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.94,0:23:11.80,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen one like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.13,0:23:18.17,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Based on the size of its battery, \Nit probably doesn't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.52,0:23:22.30,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,But this form and performance...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.30,0:23:24.28,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,How fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.35,0:23:27.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Do you like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.19,0:23:31.19,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still a long way from trusting him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.19,0:23:36.64,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,but if he tires of waiting and \Nasks you about me, tell him this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.38,0:23:43.98,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,That I'm his sister from another domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.00,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:47.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're in Kanazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.24,0:23:53.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You wish to challenge the \Ngreat detective Mouri Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.64,0:23:55.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:24:00.08,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.81,0:24:06.75,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.00,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Kaga Hyakumangoku Mystery \NTour (Kanazawa Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.64,0:24:14.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "Kaga \NHyakumangoku Mystery Tour, Kanazawa Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:35.03,Shoulder,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Shoulder Bag
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.54,0:24:32.57,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.57,0:24:35.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A shoulder bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:36.81,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Next week we're all going to Kanazawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:40.07,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.81,0:24:38.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm excited for the Kagawa hot springs!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.03,0:24:39.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't cause any trouble.
